esenting a complete phenotypic rescue (Extended Data Fig. 1d, e). We then performed the reverse crossing experiment to test whether glr1/2 sperm were incapable of achieving fertilization. We found that outcrossing rates dropped markedly when the glr1/2 mutant expressing},
author = {Ortiz-ram{\'{i}}rez, Carlos and erwan Michard and Simon, Alexander A and Damineli, Daniel C and marcela Hern{\'{a}}ndez-Coronado and Becker, J{\"{o}}rg D and Feij{\'{o}}, Jos{\'{e}} A},
